<section id="ember178" style="display: none;" class="pv-highlights-section pv-profile-section artdeco-container-card artdeco-card ember-view">
<section id="ember97" class="pv-profile-section pv-about-section artdeco-card p5 mt4 ember-view">

I  am a teaching assistant professor at the Department of Computer Science, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. I teach database and data science courses. My research interests are broadly in the field of databases, with a focus on data management. I am particularly interested in applying machine learning methods to various problems of modern data management systems: scientific workflow provenance, data citation and managing file-based datasets. Please visit my personal website (www.alawini.com) for more information.
<section id="ember185" class="pv-profile-section pv-recent-activity-section-v2 artdeco-card p5 mt4 ember-view">

Congratulations, Wade!
Well deserved. The best way to spread knowledge is to "tear down the walls around the gardens". Keep up the good work.

<div class="inline-show-more-text
    inline-show-more-text--is-collapsed
    
    
    pv-entity__description t-14 t-black t-normal
    " style="line-height:2rem;max-height:8rem;">
I teach senior undergraduate and graduate level computer science classes at PSU.

<div class="inline-show-more-text
    inline-show-more-text--is-collapsed
    
    
    pv-entity__description t-14 t-black t-normal mb4
    " style="line-height:2rem;max-height:8rem;">

Researched and developed tools and techniques that combines machine learning (CRFs and SVMs) and relational database methods (Data Profiling and Schema Matching) for determining connections among scientific datasets.

Contributed to the development of SQLShare System (Database-as-a-Service for Scientists) by developing a cloud-based application that enables SQLShare users to upload datasets stored in MS-Excel files.

<div class="inline-show-more-text
    inline-show-more-text--is-collapsed
    
    
    pv-entity__description t-14 t-black t-normal
    " style="line-height:2rem;max-height:8rem;">
•Responsible of managing the two largest academic computing labs in PSU campus (Broadway housing lab and Neuberger Hall Lab).
* Provide technical and administrative support for over 30 student employees.

<div class="inline-show-more-text
    inline-show-more-text--is-collapsed
    
    
    pv-entity__description t-14 t-black t-normal
    " style="line-height:2rem;max-height:8rem;">
• Established Judi IT department which includes: hiring IT professionals, ordering IT infrastructure equipment and designing and implementing IT systems infrastructure.
• Developed Judi Payroll and Administration System.

• Managed and participated in Judi in-house ERP System Project. This project includes the development of Warehouse Management System, Sales and Distribution System and Production and Quality Control System.

• Managed and participated in Judi Warehouse Automation System. This system includes the installation of forklift mounted computers, product scanning devices and the wireless network that connected those systems to main servers.
• Awarded Judi Best Performance Award in 2008.
